# World Geography O/X
> Countries, oceans, and landmarks
@languageCode: en
// Swiq — https://swiq.jiun.dev/set/seed.en.geography.world-geo/

The capital of France is Paris. | O | Paris is the capital and largest city of France.
The Nile is a river in Africa. | O | The Nile flows through north-eastern Africa and is one of the world's longest rivers.
Australia is both a country and a continent. | O | Australia is a single country that also forms its own continent.
The Pacific Ocean is the largest ocean on Earth. | O | The Pacific is the largest and deepest of Earth's oceans.
Mount Everest is the highest mountain above sea level. | O | At about 8,849 metres, Everest is the highest mountain above sea level, in the Himalayas.
Japan is an island country in Asia. | O | Japan is made up of many islands off the east coast of Asia.
The capital of the United States is New York City. | X | The capital of the United States is Washington, D.C. New York is its largest city.
The Amazon River is in Europe. | X | The Amazon River is in South America, not Europe.
Africa is the smallest continent. | X | Africa is the second-largest continent; Australia/Oceania is the smallest.
The Sahara Desert is located in South America. | X | The Sahara Desert is in northern Africa.
Russia is smaller in area than Italy. | X | Russia is the largest country in the world by area, far larger than Italy.
The Atlantic Ocean is larger than the Pacific Ocean. | X | The Pacific Ocean is larger than the Atlantic Ocean.
The capital of Japan is Tokyo. | O | Tokyo is Japan's capital and one of the most populous metropolitan areas in the world.
The capital of Australia is Sydney. | X | Australia's capital is Canberra; Sydney is its largest city.
Brazil is the largest country in South America. | O | Brazil covers nearly half of South America, making it the continent's largest country by area and population.
The Statue of Liberty is located in London. | X | The Statue of Liberty stands in New York Harbor in the United States; it was a gift from France.
The capital of Canada is Toronto. | X | Canada's capital is Ottawa; Toronto is the country's largest city.
The equator divides the Earth into the Northern and Southern Hemispheres. | O | The equator is an imaginary line around the middle of the Earth that separates the Northern Hemisphere from the Southern Hemisphere.
Canada shares a land border with the United States. | O | Canada and the United States share the world's longest international land border.
The capital of Brazil is Rio de Janeiro. | X | Brazil's capital is Brasília, a planned city that replaced Rio de Janeiro as capital in 1960.
The capital of Italy is Rome. | O | Rome is Italy's capital and largest city, famous for its long history.
Mount Kilimanjaro is located in Europe. | X | Kilimanjaro is in Tanzania and is the highest mountain in Africa.
The Arctic Ocean is the warmest ocean on Earth. | X | The Arctic is the coldest and smallest of the world's oceans, largely covered by sea ice.
Antarctica is the coldest continent on Earth. | O | Antarctica holds the record for the lowest temperatures ever measured on Earth and is covered by a thick ice sheet.
Switzerland has a long ocean coastline. | X | Switzerland is a landlocked country in the Alps with no coastline at all.
Egypt is a country in Africa. | O | Egypt lies in the north-east corner of Africa, with a small part of its territory, the Sinai Peninsula, in Asia.
The Alps are a mountain range in Europe. | O | The Alps stretch across several European countries, including France, Switzerland, Italy, and Austria.
The capital of South Korea is Busan. | X | South Korea's capital is Seoul; Busan is the country's second-largest city and main port.
Greenland is the largest island in the world. | O | Greenland is the world's largest island; Australia is bigger but is counted as a continent.
England and France are connected by a bridge. | X | There is no bridge between them; they are linked by the Channel Tunnel, an undersea rail tunnel beneath the English Channel.
The Andes mountain range is in South America. | O | The Andes run along the western edge of South America and form the longest mountain range on land.
Madagascar is an island off the coast of India. | X | Madagascar lies in the Indian Ocean off the south-east coast of Africa, not near India.
The shore of the Dead Sea is the highest point on Earth's land surface. | X | The Dead Sea shore is the lowest land point on Earth, more than 400 metres below sea level.
The Mediterranean Sea lies between Europe and Africa. | O | The Mediterranean separates southern Europe from northern Africa and connects to the Atlantic through the Strait of Gibraltar.
New Zealand is part of the continent of Asia. | X | New Zealand is an island country in Oceania, in the south-western Pacific Ocean.
The Great Barrier Reef is located off the coast of Australia. | O | The Great Barrier Reef, the world's largest coral reef system, lies off the north-east coast of Australia.
